HEADWORD: Snipebill
<hw>Snipe"bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
plane for cutting deep grooves in moldings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bolt by which the body of a cart is fastened to
the axle.</def> <mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snipefish</ent>⟦br⟧
